---

# Styling Strategy

Follow the project's existing styling conventions.

Do not introduce a new styling framework.

---

# Tailwind

Use Tailwind for:

- Layout
- Flex/Grid
- Spacing
- Responsive utilities

Avoid creating utility CSS that Tailwind already provides.

---

# CSS

Use CSS files for:

- Complex animations
- Component-specific styling
- Media queries
- Shared reusable styles

Extend existing CSS before creating a new CSS file.

---

# Design Tokens

Always reuse existing CSS variables.

Never hardcode colors if a design token exists.

Prefer existing spacing and typography variables.

---

# Reuse First

Before writing CSS:

- Search for an existing class.
- Search for existing utilities.
- Search for an existing animation.

Reuse first.

---

# Animations

Prefer CSS transitions.

Avoid unnecessary Framer Motion.

No layout shift.

No scroll hitching.

---

# Responsive

Desktop first if following existing patterns.

Maintain existing breakpoints.

Never break mobile layouts.

---

# Before Completion

Verify:

- No duplicate CSS
- No unused classes
- Existing styles reused